items.title: Building Your Own Digital Music and Distribution Label

visible_instructors.title: Amed Clinton
visible_instructors.name: Amed
visible_instructors.job_title: Audio Engineer at Little Dipper Media

items.headline: A Quick Guide To Getting Started
objectives_summary: Students will know how to set up their music business and acquire their DBA or Assumed Name, get their EIN free of charge directly from the IRS, and the process of setting up their business account.

Students will know how to acquire their own essential components for music distribution such as their UPC/EAN, International Standard Recording Codes (ISRC), and how to register works with Nielson Soundscan.
Students will know how to electronically copyright their works, as well as register for BMI or ASCAP and their importance for mechanical and publishing royalty collection.
